Responsibilities

Handle C&B functions including monthly payroll, staff movement, attendance & leave management and final payment calculation;
Handle MPF, taxation & medical administration, and work injury cases;
Retail section update & maintain of employee information in HR system, support the system enhancement project;
Prepare reports on a regular basis;

Assist in staff disciplinary and labor dispute cases;

Participate in ad-hoc projects and duties as required.

Requirements

Diploma or above in Human Resources Management or related disciplines;
1 year of solid experience on C&B functions in a sizable organization, especially in payroll area is preferred;
Detailed & quality-oriented and strong sense of accountability;
Good numerical sense, good command of both spoken & written in English and Chinese;
Well-versed in Employment Ordinance and other HR-related legislation;
Proficiency in MS Office and experiences of using HRIS;
Immediate availability is highly preferred.

We offer

5-day work week
Medical Benefits
Performance Bonus
Staff Purchase Discounts
Staff Recreation Activity
Shuttle Bus Service
Education Sponsorship

