Job Description:

General duties of Hr and Admin Assistant, such as data input and filing, 
Handle full spectrum of HR functions which include but not limit to recruitment, compensation & benefits, training & development, and staff relations;
Scouring CV and perform candidate search in the market to identify the right candidates;
Review CVs and credentials for suitability of skills, experience, and knowledge in relation to position requirements using appropriate selection techniques;
Handling ad-hoc assignments.
Requirements:

Associate Degree/Degree holder in Human Resources Management or related discipline;
Proficiency in Microsoft Office;
Proficiency in Mandarin, English, and Cantonese, both spoken and written
Immediate available or short notice is preferred
We provide attractive remuneration package and fringe benefits for the right candidate.  Interested parties please send detailed resume with current & expected salaries via “Apply Now”.

Responsibilities:

Perform reception duties including telephone calls, greeting and serving visitors in professional manner;
Provide general office administrative work and clerical supports;
Support ad-hoc assignments.

Requirements: 

Diploma in Hospitality or related disciplines preferred;
1 year's working experience in service field preferred, fresh graduate will also be considered;
Strong sense of responsibility, proactive, energetic, pleasant and customer-oriented;
Good PC knowledge in MS Office & Chinese Word Processing;
Proficiency in both written & spoken English and Chinese including Mandarin;
Immediate available is preferred.

Working Location: Hong Kong Science Park, Tai Po

We offer 5-day working week and an attractive remuneration package. Interest parties please click Apply Now. For company details, please visit www.purapharm.com.

Our Company is an equal opportunity employer. All personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only, while the personal data of the unsuccessful applicants will be destroyed within 6 months after the recruitment process.

The Role
To cope with our aggressive growth and expansion plan, we are inviting high caliber individuals to join our fast growth team.  You will have a chance to work at a fast-paced mission driven company that brings material science to life and benefit the mass.  We are bringing business disruption and new hygiene standard to the world with the introduction of new photocatalyst products and services. With the continuous R&D and business innovation, we are thrilled to develop the next generation technology that safeguards everyday life.  

Responsibilities

Communicate and manage the recruitment requests of BUs/Hiring Managers;
Develop and manage recruitment process effectively from posting job advertisements, screening resumes, conducting interviews, confirming offer and recruitment project management;
Provide end-to-end recruitment process to ensure hiring needs are fulfilled timely and effectively, support hiring managers to further develop and strengthen the talent pool;
Develop effective hiring channels and methodologies for recruitment pipeline;
Prepare hiring tracking reports and liaise with hiring manager on the progress;
Prepare HR reports and data analysis on staff turnover, retention, career development, etc;
Assist in any other HR duties as assigned.
Requirements

Degree in Human Resources Management, Business Management or related disciplines;
Minimum 3 years of solid recruiting experience in fast-paced business environment with proven expertise from FMCG or consumer healthcare market is a MUST;
Mature, self-motivated, ability to prioritize multiple tasks and work under pressure;
Strong PC skills, well-versed in Microsoft applications and Chinese word processing
Immediate available is highly preferred;
Fluent in written and spoken English, Cantonese and Mandarin.
We offer the right candidate attractive remuneration package and outstanding prospects for career advancement and development.  The right candidate will progress career in a forward thinking and dynamic business with exciting growth plans.  If you are qualified and interested, please send your full resume with current & expected salary and availability by clicking "APPLY".

All information collected will be treated as strictly confidential and used for recruitment purposes only. (Only shortlisted candidates will be notified)

工作範圍與職責
建立與維護包括但不限於人事合同、文件、檔案、考勤記錄及其他基礎資料；
負責香港員工薪酬及福利，包括工資、補貼、強積金、個人入息稅，保險及其他福利（如適用）的計算及統計，生成和維護資料庫，編制人力成本月報、年報，以及上級單位或公司管理需要的統計結果與報告；
參與人事執行資訊系統優化工作；
協助評估審查人事政策、制度流程適用性，提出改進建議，跟進後續的維護與優化工作；
協助進行人力資源市場研究、人力資源戰略分析和提出解決方案建議；
負責公司人員職崗管理（招聘、提聘、調崗、離退）、考核管理，培訓等具體工作；
在部門負責人指導下，編制香港辦公室人事行政年度預算；
做好部門交辦的其他工作。

Job Descriptions:


Reporting to the Head of HR and Administration in providing full spectrum of human resources functions including but not limited to compensation and benefits, recruitment and selection, performance management, taxation, MPF, policy review, insurance renewal, system implementation and ad-hoc projects.


Participate in formulating HR related policies and procedures in compliance with legal requirements, company standard and HR practice;
Provide support for annual salary and benefit review, salary benchmarking and benefits surveys;
Ensure accuracy and monthly payroll calculation for both Headquarter and subsidiaries;
Manage attendance and leave data in HRIS on regular basis to facilitate report generation and payroll processing;
Maintain updated HR records in human resources systems and personal file system;
Prepare regular HR reports, annual budget and forecast required by the Group or Management;
Participate in HR system & advancement project;
Support HR ad-hoc duty assigned by Supervisor.

Requirements:


Bachelor Degree holder in Human Resources Management or related discipline;
Minimum 3-5 years of relevant working experience with hands-on experience in payroll and C&B function; with experience in Chinese Enterprises is an advantage;
Well versed in Employment Ordinance, MPF and other related statutory regulations;
Independent, well-organized with positive working attitude and ability to handle multi-tasks;
Strong command of written and spoken English & Chinese including Mandarin is a MUST;
Immediately available is preferred;
Candidate with less experience will be considered as HR Officer.

Responsibilities:

Handle and coordinate routine HR functions, including recruitment advertisement posting, interview arrangement, onboarding arrangement and so on;
Participate in job fair, recruitment day and other recruitment activities;
Assist in developing HR projects including on-the-job training, team-building activities and other staff relations activities;
Assist senior executives for the development of an effective recruitment channel for employer branding and talent sourcing;
Communicate and coordinate with internal and external stakeholders, including secondary and tertiary education institutions;
Perform any ad hoc projects as assigned

Requirements:

Diploma or above in Human Resources Management, Business Administrations or related disciplines;
Minimum 2 to 3 years relevant working experience in the field of human resources, candidate with less experience will be considered as Human Resources Assistant;
Well versed in Hong Kong Employment Ordinance and related legislation;
Excellent interpersonal and communication skills;
Responsible, fast-paced, self-motivated, well-organized and detail-minded;
Good command of written and spoken English and Chinese;
Proficiency in Microsoft Office applications (Word, Excel & PowerPoint) and Chinese word processing;
Immediately available is highly preferred;
Fresh graduates are welcome to apply

Reporting to the Human Resources Director, the HR & Admin Officer will be responsible for the following duties:
 

Key Responsibilities


Responsible for full range of HR administration work including but not limited to MPF, insurance enrolment, orientation contents;
Handle onboarding and exit procedures to ensure all required documents are properly processed;
Create and maintain employee data records and personnel documents, maintain HR software system;
Maintain and update annual leave record;
Supports payroll management and statutory requirements from the Inland Revenue Department;
Be one of the HR contact points for general employees’ inquiries;
Handle work visa applications for expatriate staff;
Assist all general office administration and ad hoc projects as required

 Requirements 

A university graduate with at least 3 years solid experience as a HR Generalist;
Good command of written and spoken English & Chinese, Mandarin is a plus;
Meticulous and attention to detail;
Excellent communication and problem-solving skills;
Well organized, self-motivated, able to work independently and multi-tasking;
Can-do attitude and a team player

Interested parties, please submit with your detailed resume stating your current and expected salary.

 All information provided will be treated with strict confidence and will be used for recruitment purposes only.

Responsibilities:


Assist in all round office administration including but not limited to procurement of office equipment's and office supplies, filing, office equipment's maintenance, stationeries and pantry’s supplies etc.;
Work closely with internal departments and business units to provide HR support for frontline staff;
Provide support on full spectrum of Human Resources services including but not limited to recruitment and selection, compensation and benefits administration, MPF administration, performance management, employee relations and taxation issues, etc; 
Responsible for monthly payroll calculation including commission, incentives & bonus scheme calculations;
Responsible for the duty roster, staff record and leave record;
Prepare statistical report and presentation materials for management review; 
Business and personal support to Director;
Participate in ad-hoc duties or project as assigned;

Mature and can work independently;

 Requirements:

High Diploma holder in Business Administration, Human Resources or related discipline;
At least 3 years Admin and Human Resources experiences in Medical industry will be an advantage;
Medical beauty or Clinic experience is highly preferable;;
Responsible, well organized and willing to learn; 
A good team player with strong interpersonal and problem solving skills;
Good knowledge in HK Employment Ordinance and related regulations;
Good command of Cantonese, Mandarin and English;

We offer on these roles

